 JOHANNESBURG - Health Minister, Joe Phaahla says the loan by the World Bank will ensure government accelerates its COVID-19 response. The World Bank granted South Africa a loan of R11.4 billion. READ: COVID-19 in SA | World Bank approves $750m loan Government asked for the loan as part of efforts to address the socio-economic impact of COVID-19 and bolster economic recovery. The loan comes just ahead of Finance Minister Enoch Godongwana’s maiden budget speech in February.